&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Robotics Engineering, Computer Science, Engineering, or related technical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1+ years of experience working with Autonomous Mobile Robots (AMRs), with demonstrated expertise in deploying warehouse software or logistics systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must hold a valid passport and the ability to travel throughout the U.S., Canada, and Mexico as needed to support deployments and customer engagements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong experience with Linux or Unix systems, ROS (Robot Operating System), and SLAM-based navigation&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity in warehouse/fulfillment center mapping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical knowledge of IT or complex professional systems deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift, pull, and push up to 50lbs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-motivated and able to solve problems independently and in customer settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated proficiency in Spanish (written and verbal) required to effectively communicate with Spanish-speaking clients and team members.&lt;/li&gt;
